      • readPlayers

        private static Player[] readPlayers(java.lang.String filename)
                             throws java.lang.Exception
        This method reads a players methods from the file and creates an array of players. The method is passed the filename of the team. You will need to open the file returning a File object. Then you will need to create a Scanner object and count the records calling countRecords passing fin and nothing else. Close the file and then reopen it. Make an array of players and then fill that array with player objects.
        Parameters:
        filename - The filename for the file containing that teams players
        Returns:
        Player [] Each teams array of players
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - For the Scanner object used to read from the File
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the filename is null or empty
